King William’s Town - A 42-year-old man was arrested for the alleged rape of his eight-year-old niece at Nomaheya village near King William's Town, Eastern Cape police said on Monday. Police spokesperson Captain Jackson Manatha said the uncle was arrested on Sunday, after the girl told her mother when she returned home that her uncle had raped her. “The allegation is that the mother of the child left her two children with her brother on Thursday. It is alleged that the victim was sleeping at her uncle's place with her sister on Saturday... The uncle sent her sister to the tavern to buy beer for him. The suspect raped the victim while the sister was at the tavern,” he said. The man was expected to appear in the Ngqamakhwe Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. African News Agency